    "body": "## Problem\r\n`nvim_set_option_value` lacks features present in other methods of setting options. #38420\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nAdd `operation` field to `nvim_set_option_value`, which takes an enum of \"set\", \"append\", \"prepend\", or \"remove\". This allows it to function similar to `:set opt=`, `:set opt+=`, etc.\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n- `set` is unnecessary, but I like it for making the logic very consistent\r\n-  ~~Does not fix #39038. I didn't change any of the append, prepend, or remove logic. All that will need careful inspection to ensure consistency with the docs. I think that'll be easier to manage as a separate PR.~~ Using C logic should make these consistent.\r\n\r\n## TODO\r\n- Docs\r\n- Tests\r\n\r\nclose #38420\r\nclose #14888\r\nclose #15720\r\nclose #39038",
    "closed_at": null,
